						<summary>

						<p>On a beam of the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of betel nuts to a god on the occasion of <hi rend="italic">Dīpāvaḷi</hi> by Kēṇikāṟa Echiseṭṭi, described as the son of the One Thousand of Lokkiguṇḍi which is said to have been an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> gifted by Rāma.</p>						

